dat_errors = metaumbrella::view.errors.umbrella(dat_sleep)
## WARNING:
## - Some rows of the original dataset have been removed based on the 'discard' column inputs: rows = 153, 154, 155, 156, 157, 181, 182, 183, 184, 185, 188, 189, 190, 191, 193, 195, 241, 242, 243, 248, 249, 250, 260, 261, 262, 263, 265, 267, 269, 271, 273, 275, 278, 282, 331, 336 (only a warning, not an error).
## - Some but not all effect sizes are reversed for a factor. Check this is what you want (this is only a warning, not an error).
res = umbrella(dat_sleep, mult.level=TRUE,
               verbose = FALSE)

DT::datatable(summary(res), 
              rownames = FALSE,
              options = list(  # options
                scrollX = TRUE,
                dom = c('ft'), 
                scrollY = "600px", 
                pageLength = 600,
                autoWidth = TRUE,
                columnDefs = list(
                  list(width = '110px',
                       targets = "_all"),
                  list(className = 'dt-center', 
                       targets = "_all"))))
evid = add.evidence(res, criteria="GRADE")

DT::datatable(summary(evid), 
              rownames = FALSE,
              options = list(  # options
                scrollX = TRUE,
                dom = c('ft'), 
                scrollY = "600px", 
                pageLength = 600,
                autoWidth = TRUE,
                columnDefs = list(
                  list(width = '110px',
                       targets = "_all"),
                  list(className = 'dt-center', 
                       targets = "_all"))))
sum_evid = summary(evid)
 
sum_evid$I2 = as.numeric(sum_evid$I2)
## Warning: NAs introduced by coercion
sum_evid$factor = sum_evid$Factor
dat_plot = left_join(sum_evid, dat_fact)
## Joining, by = "factor"
dat_plot$Population = substr(dat_plot$Population, 1, 20) 
dat_plot$Intervention = substr(dat_plot$Intervention, 1, 20) 
dat_plot$Outcome = substr(dat_plot$Outcome, 1, 20) 
dat_plot$Factor = substr(dat_plot$Factor, 1, 20) 

forest(dat_plot,
       layout = "RevMan5",
       subgroup = "Class",
       subgroup.name = "Class",
      leftcols = c("Population", "Intervention",
                   "Outcome", "total_n", "Factor",
                   "effect.ci"),
       leftlabs = c("Population", "Intervention",
                    "Outcome", "n-sample", "Factor",
                    "eSMD + 95% CI")
)

downloadthis::download_this(
  dat_errors,
  output_name = "errors",
  output_extension = ".xlsx",
